The Party goes in with everything that moves: printers, lawyers, the teachers' networks opening provincial doors for TD brigades. In the plants the electricians notice who showed up early. So does don Fidel, whose organization has never forgiven a debt or forgotten an address, and whose gunmen have a longer payroll than yours.

@exterior
go-to: post_event
on-arrival: td_apoyo = 1; sup_electricians += 4; charrismo -= 1; expediente += 2; huelgas += 4

Solidarity with a firewall: the paper opens its pages, the collections run, the marches swell with your contingents — and the Party's own cells stay structurally clear of the TD's fate, whatever it proves to be. Galván accepts the arrangement with the dry courtesy of a man cataloguing who committed what, for reference at the accounting that always comes.

@margen
go-to: post_event
on-arrival: td_apoyo = 0; sup_electricians -= 3; sup_workers -= 1; fac_renovadores -= 2

The editorial wishes the electricians well in the passive voice. It is prudent; the CTM's cemetery of challengers is real. But the most vital workers' movement of the epoch has measured the Party's distance to the centimeter, and the class has a long memory for who was in the plaza and who sent regards.
